# JavaScript Class Structure

```javascript
class Animal {
  constructor(name, type) {
    this.name = name;
    this.type = type;
  }
  speak() {
    console.log(`${this.name} makes a noise.`);
  }
}

// Creating an instance
const dog = new Animal('Dog', 'Mammal');
dog.speak(); // Dog makes a noise.
```

### Class Features:

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Constructor | Initializes new objects |
| Methods | Functions inside the class |
| Instances | Individual realizations of the class |

# Inheritance in JavaScript

```javascript
class Animal {
  constructor(name) {
    this.name = name;
  }
  speak() {
    console.log(`${this.name} makes a noise.`);
  }
}

class Dog extends Animal {
  constructor(name, breed) {
    super(name);  // Call the parent class constructor
    this.breed = breed;
  }
  speak() {
    console.log(`${this.name} barks.`);
  }
}

// Creating an instance
const beagle = new Dog('Beagle', 'Beagle');
beagle.speak(); // Beagle barks.
```

### Inheritance Features:

| Feature | Benefit |
|---------|---------|
| `extends` Keyword | Enables class inheritance |
| `super` Keyword | Calls the parent class's constructor |
| Method Overriding | Allows specific behavior |

# Advanced Class Features

```javascript
class Rectangle {
  #height; // Private field
  #width; // Private field
  constructor(height, width) {
    this.#height = height;
    this.#width = width;
  }
  get area() {
    return this.#calculateArea();
  }
  #calculateArea() {
    return this.#height * this.#width;
  }
  static isSquare(rectangle) {
    return rectangle.#height === rectangle.#width;
  }
}

// Usage
const rectangle = new Rectangle(20, 10);
console.log(rectangle.area); // 200
console.log(Rectangle.isSquare(rectangle)); // false
```

### Key Concepts:

| Concept | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Private Fields | Encapsulate data within class |
| Static Methods | Class-level utility functions |
| Getter Methods | Access properties |
